2. Clicks Save| C{Client-side Validation}
-->|Valid| D[Create Note Object]
-->|Invalid| E[Show Validation Error]
----> F{Network Connection}
-->|Connected| G[POST /notes to Server]
-->|Success| H[Update UI with New Note]
-->|Error| I[Show Error to User]

Explanation:

1. The user writes a new note in the text field.
2. The user clicks the Save button.
3. Client-side validation checks if the input is valid.
  If valid, a new note object is created.
  If invalid, a validation error is shown.
4. The client checks the network connection.
  If connected, it sends a POST request to the server with the new note data.
  If not connected, an error is shown to the user.
5. On successful server response, the UI is updated with the new note.
  If there's an error, it is shown to the user.
